# Embedded hardare

Most of todays embedded boards are based on [AMD Geode](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AMD_Geode) LX platform. Some of the [mini
PCs](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Linux_mini_computers) are:

* [Linutop](http://www.linutop.com/)
* [Koolu](http://www.koolu.com/)


## Pros

* Silent
* Small physical footprint
* Robust
* Low energy consumption


## Cons

* Long order times
* `acpi=off` to boot successfully
* Needs some patches with the video drivers
* No [[networking]]
* You need to arrange the monitor, keyboard and mouse for the device
* [Sluggish CPU](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amd_geode#AMD_Geode)


